        <br />
        <br />
        This is Adriana Meunié. She spent just a few days in Ibiza for the contemporary art fair and gained a multitude of inspiration
        from her visit. Her highlight piece above stole the show and can fetch a price of R23,000. Meunié blurs the lines between
        art, design, textiles, and cultures. She blends elements from past, present, and future. To create her art, she uses 
        materials such as wool and wood.
